This paper is primarily focused on the requirements for localization of autonomous vehicles, which falls under the field of robotics (cs.RO). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of perception and control for safe operation, which are also key areas of research in robotics. The paper also mentions the use of machine learning and computer vision for perception, which are subfields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV), respectively. The paper also discusses the safety integrity level, which is a concept in systems engineering and control theory (cs.SY). Finally, the paper uses statistical analysis to derive error bounds and accuracy requirements, which is a topic in machine learning and statistics (cs.LG).
